 [FILES] A medical worker  (Photo by OLGA MALTSEVA / AFP)  While listing some of the NTDs to include onchocerciasis, lymphatic filariasis, soil-transmitted helminths, trachoma, schistosomiasis, buruli ulcer, snake bite, leprosy, human African trypanosomiasis, Guinea worms, yaws and loiasis, he said that with good sanitation and proper hygiene, the diseases could be checked.
